## 🚀 **Next Steps - Deploy to AWS:**

### **Option 1: AWS Amplify (Recommended)**
1. Go to [AWS Amplify Console](https://console.aws.amazon.com/amplify/)
2. Click **"New app"** → **"Host web app"**
3. Select **GitHub** as source
4. Choose repository: `ashish12513/cudos-dashboard-app`
5. Amplify will auto-detect `amplify.yml`
6. **Configure Environment Variables**:
   ```
   AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_access_key
   AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_secret_key
   AWS_REGION=ap-south-1
   AWS_ACCOUNT_ID=737185589565
   QUICKSIGHT_DASHBOARD_ID=cudos-v5
   NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your_random_secret_key
   NEXTAUTH_URL=https://your-amplify-url.amplifyapp.com
   ```
7. **Deploy!**

### **Option 2: EC2 with Docker**
```bash
# On your EC2 instance
git clone https://github.com/ashish12513/cudos-dashboard-app.git
cd cudos-dashboard-app
cp .env.example .env.local
# Edit .env.local with your AWS credentials
docker-compose up -d
```

